<br>
&quot;You pick your class and live with the challenge that they bring.If you pick a utitilty class then that is your role,live with it.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;If I wanted to solo I would have been a druid&quot;<br>
<br>
I picked a druid because I liked the idea of being a druid. I like the roleplay aspect of a druid. I don't want to roleplay a cleric. I certainly didn't pick a druid because I wanted to solo. I don't really like soloing. I hate quad kiting. Why should I be prevented from getting a group? =)<br>
<br>
&quot;How do we get to that point if all of a sudden we can be shut out of xp groups by a druid?&quot;<br>
<br>
Actually, this balances it out. At the moment, clerics kind of exclude druids from groups. Shamans have their own things to offer groups, but druids not really so much. Improving druids healing abilities makes it easier fro druids to get a group. The argument of a lot of clerics is that druids don't NEED groups. Sure, they can get experience when not in a group. But half the fun of EQ is the social aspect. Plus the majority of places are very difficult for druids to solo, and thus the majority of quests cannot be fulfilled by soloing. We may not need groups, but we still want them, no less than you will still want groups if Verant makes it easy for a cleric to solo.<br>
<br>
Also, druids and clerics would not be mutually exclusive. Someone's not going to turn down a cleric just because they have a druid in the group because in that instance the druid would turn nuker. Even if it was a toss up between taking a druid and a cleric, I would still say the cleric would be taken. If a group needs a healer, they want the best possible healer e.g. cleric. Druids will still not be as good at healing as clerics.<br>
<br>
Decius Silverdawn<br>
56th Preserver<br>
Resolution <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uxyloxfv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>XyloxFV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 129<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/26/02 2:54:14 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm45.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=61.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Not-quite-CH for Druids and Shamans</span><hr size=1> I'm sorry Decius, you are just wrong.<br>
<br>
First of all, druid already are group friendly.  They are perhaps the most group friendly class in EQ.  Sow, heals, DS, Succor, AoE... They have it all.. They are welcome in lots of groups.<br>
<br>
Clerics have nothing to offer besides stand and CH every 5 minutes.  We are already passed over in favor of Shamen and in lots of cases druids too.<br>
<br>
And it makes total sense.  I don't blame groups for not wanting/needing clerics.  It's verant's fault.  I mean take a place like Velks.  If I play conservatively, my mana never drops below 80%.  That 80% mana is a total waste of resources for the group.   There's not much else I can do with that 80% mana... I could throw a few nukes in, but they suck.  Now take a druid.  You give a druid anything near CH, and he can now use that 80% mana to DS, nuke, snare, dot, etc etc etc.  You see the point.  There is absolutely no reason to ever have a cleric in a group again.  We offer nothing except wasted resources.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  clerics kind of exclude druids from groups<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
I'm sorry, this is just false.<br>
<br>
<br>
I'm truely happy that you play the game for fun, and the social aspect.  If you can't find groups, it's probably just the places you are looking, not because the group already has a cleric.  I'm a cleric and I'm grouped with a druid 95% of the groups I'm in.  <br>
<br>
There has to be some penalty for being able to do everything.  Druids are overpowered now.  In a world where people weren't worried about raining on each others parade, people would screaming for druids to be nerfed.  I don't buy into nerfing myself, so I offer a different approach.<br>
<br>
Druids and Shamen are fine.. Just leave them be.<br>
<br>
Just like Nilaini said, There aren't enough clerics out there?? Try making them interesting to play.  If we could 1/4 the stuff druids could, people might actually play them... BTW half the clerics you see on FV aren't even being actively played, they are just bots.<br>
<br>
I'm sorry if this sounds harsh, but druids should just sit down and be happy with what they have.. because they have everything.<br>
<br>
Xylox <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=decius1>Decius1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 37<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/26/02 11:05:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm45.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=61.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Not-quite-CH for Druids and Shamans</span><hr size=1> Druid as a primary healer is exceedingly difficult at the high levels. You can do it in Velks if you're KEIed but otherwise you need a cleric. To heal up someone with 4K hitpoints costs a LOT of mana without a cleric. In most circumstances, especially post 50, druids can only heal well enough to be a back up, secondary or bridge healer. Back up / secondary / bridge healers are not essential. Primary healers are. Q.E.D.<br>
<br>
Edit: Almost forgot what I was posting for. The new experience system which rewards the slaying of greater beasts over the slaying of multiple lesser beasts - this may have a side effect of nerfing quad kiting and generally making soloing less rewarding than it is now. I wait in eager anticipation.<br>
